# Calculator navigation

Do **not** add a "Back to Immigration Tools" (or similar text back link) on calculator pages.

Use the **close (X) button** in the page header instead — same pattern as `CitizenshipEligibilityCalculator`:

- Top-right of the header row (`flex ... justify-between`)
- Icon-only `Link` with `aria-label="Close and return to calculators"`
- Default destination: `/calculators`
- Classes: `h-9 w-9`, rounded border, white background, X SVG icon

```tsx
<Link
  href="/calculators"
  className="flex h-9 w-9 shrink-0 items-center justify-center self-start rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white text-slate-600 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-slate-300 hover:bg-slate-50 hover:text-slate-900 focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-brand-500/30"
  aria-label="Close and return to calculators"
>
  {/* X icon */}
</Link>
```

Reference implementations: `components/CitizenshipEligibilityCalculator.tsx`, `components/GreenCardWaitTimeCalculator.tsx`.

Secondary cross-links between related tools (e.g. H-1B wage ↔ lottery) may stay as text links in the header — but never replace the close button with a back link.
